        <p>
          Dedicated GEO monitoring platforms automate the query-sampling process and provide dashboards for citation frequency trends, competitive share of voice, and alert workflows. They are worth evaluating once your manual measurement process is established and you understand which metrics matter most for your programme. Starting with a monitoring platform before understanding your baseline metrics often leads to data overload rather than insight. For a guide to evaluating these platforms, see <a href="/geo-tools/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO tools</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-dark mt-16">
        <h2 id="measurement-framework" class="anchor-top">The GEO Measurement Framework: Six Steps</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>A repeatable GEO measurement framework is a six-step cycle that runs monthly, produces a single consolidated scorecard, and generates clear optimisation priorities for the following period.</strong> The steps below are sequenced for implementation — complete each before moving to the next when setting up for the first time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border hair">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b hair bg-white/[.03]">
