      </div>

      <div class="prose-dark mt-8">
        <p>
          The scorecard produced in step six should be a single document — typically a spreadsheet — that records all four metrics month-over-month alongside a brief annotation of any interventions made. This running record is essential for attributing metric movements to specific actions. Without it, you cannot determine whether a citation frequency increase was driven by a content update, an entity schema change, or an external factor such as a model update. If you would like GEOoptimised to run this framework on your behalf, <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">contact us</a> for details.
